The National Gun Owners Association (NGAO-Kenya) will host the inaugural 2022 Patron’s shooting Championships this Saturday at their premier shooting range in Kirigiti, Kiambu County. This match, which is open to all current International Defensive Pistol Association (IDPA) members from all over the world, has attracted a record of 120 shooters drawn from the Kenya Police Service including DCI, ATPU, ASTU and GSU among others. Also to have confirmed are officers from KDF, NIS and a good number of civilian licensed firearm holders. All top Kenyan pistol shooters have confirmed attendance and the event promises to be a show stopper. Among the top contenders participating in the different categories will be Ibrahim Ndung’u, the current IDPA Africa champion, who will feature in Masters' category Others are Eng. Robert Nyamongo, Pravir Vohra, Eric Wachira, Sammy Onyango, Mohammed Omar, Issa Issa, Kelvin Mbugua of BRC as well as the Junior Champion Jonathan Wahome. The shoot will feature 10 stages or Course of Fire (COFs) and will be run as per IDPA rules & safety protocols. According to the organisers   the event undoubtedly one of the biggest event on the 2022 shooting calendar. There will also be a fun shoot on the same day open to members of public that will run the whole day.